  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SealingFunction">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1679"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2876"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1678"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2877"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de vedação</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">sealing function</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in a SealingProcess and that consists in providing a tight interface against which a closure element bears to prevent fluid leakage through a valve.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000307">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000092"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2049"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2050"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2051"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2048"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every kettle reboiler is a reboiler that has horizontal orientation and has a separate vapour space as component part.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">refervedor tipo kettle</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">kettle reboiler</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um refervedor tipo kettle é um refervedor que possui orientação horizontal e contém um espaço de vapor separado para desengajamento vapor-líquido.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A kettle reboiler is a reboiler that has horizontal orientation and contains a separate vapour space for vapor-liquid disengagement.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type defined by specific physical configuration. Under Open World Assumption, sufficient conditions could incorrectly classify equipment with horizontal orientation and vapor space but fundamentally different purposes (e.g., horizontal separators, flash drums) as kettle reboilers. The structural differentia provides necessary conditions for the kettle reboiler maintenance/procurement category.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(KettleReboiler(x) → Reboiler(x) ∧ ∃q(HorizontalOrientation(q) ∧ hasQuality(x,q)) ∧ ∃v(SeparateVapourSpace(v) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,v)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;KETTLE REBOILER&gt; is a &lt;REBOILER&gt; that is horizontal and has a separate vapour space.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A reboiler often boils liquid coming from the bottom of a distillation column, after which the resulting vapour is returned to the distillation column.</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2623">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PressureIndicatingAndTransmissionProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000253">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">difusor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">diffuser</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um difusor é um conjunto que tem a função projetada de converter energia cinética do fluxo de fluido em energia de pressão através de desaceleração controlada em uma passagem divergente.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A diffuser is an assembly that has the designed function of converting kinetic energy of fluid flow into pressure energy through controlled deceleration in a diverging passage.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1032"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every diffuser is an assembly that bears an energy diffusion function and has a diverging channel as component part at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DIFFUSER&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that has the capability of &lt;DIFFUSING&gt; which is used in pumps to convert kinetic energy imparted by impeller to potential energy i.e. pressure head.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that contains a diverging channel-shaped chamber in which part of the kinetic energy of the fluid is converted into pressure energy.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Diffuser(x) ↔ Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(EnergyDiffusionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2694">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/EnclosureProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
