  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000285">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gas engine</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">motor a gás</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000264"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1654"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1652"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1655"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1653"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1656"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] An internal combustion engine that is a reciprocating engine in which gaseous fuel is mixed with air to form a combustible mixture in a cylinder which is fired by spark ignition.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;GAS ENGINE&gt; is an &lt;INTERNAL COMBUSTION ENGINE&gt; and a &lt;RECIPROCATING PISTON ENGINE&gt; in which gaseous fuel is mixed with air to form a combustible mixture in a cylinder which is fired by spark ignition</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An internal combustion engine that is a reciprocating engine in which gaseous fuel is mixed with air to form a combustible mixture in a cylinder which is fired by spark ignition.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um motor a gás é um motor que usa combustível gasoso como entrada, emprega um sistema de ignição por centelha e opera com um mecanismo de pistão alternativo para gerar energia mecânica.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A gas engine is an engine that uses gaseous fuel as input, employs a spark ignition system, and operates with a reciprocating piston mechanism to generate mechanical energy.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(GasEngine(x) → Engine(x) ∧ ∃f,s,r(GaseousFuelPortion(f) ∧ SparkIgnitionSystem(s) ∧ ReciprocatingPistonMechanism(r) ∧ hasInput(x,f) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,r)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every gas engine is an engine that has gaseous fuel portion as input and has spark ignition system as component part at all times and has reciprocating piston mechanism as component part at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Gas engine is defined by constructive characteristics (gaseous fuel, spark ignition, reciprocating mechanism) rather than a unique function. Under Open World Assumption, making these conditions sufficient could lead to false positives where complex hybrid engines or experimental designs with these features are automatically classified as standard gas engines when they might require different maintenance/operational categories.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/DownholeToolAssembly">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">downhole tool assembly</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">conjunto de fundo de poço de ferramenta</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000376">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every wellbore is a site that has the function of providing subsurface access and is spatially contained within a well.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] The drilled hole or borehole, including the openhole or uncased portion of the well.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] In drilling, the drilled hole.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ppdm] A Wellbore is a path of drilled footage, from the Well Origin (top/start) to a terminating point (bottom/end). Key concept: Wellbores do not need to be drilled in one continuous operation; they are defined as a path from the Well Origin to a terminating point. Clarification: There are one or more Wellbores in a planned or drilled Well, namely the original Wellbore, and a Wellbore for each intended, actual or accidental sidetrack. Each Wellbore has a unique terminating point. A deepening of an existing Wellbore is considered a new Wellbore with the same Well Origin. Note that in this case, the original terminating point will be located within the new Wellbore. Widening of an existing Wellbore does not constitute a new, separate Wellbore.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">poço perfurado</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">wellbore</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000029"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Wellbore(x) ↔ Site(x) ∧ ∃f(SubsurfaceAccessFunction(f) ∧ hasFunction(x,f)) ∧ ∃w(Well(w) ∧ spatiallyContainedIn(x,w)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A wellbore is a site that provides a drilled pathway for subsurface access and is spatially contained within a well system.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um poço perfurado é um local que fornece um caminho perfurado para acesso subsuperficial e está espacialmente contido dentro de um sistema de poço.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000317">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A Shaft that participates in mechanical energy output processes, serving as the exit point for mechanical energy transmission from a prime mover to external energy consuming equipment.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um Eixo que participa em processos de saída de energia mecânica, servindo como ponto de saída para transmissão de energia mecânica de um motor primário para equipamentos consumidores de energia externos.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (OutputShaft(x) → Shaft(x) ∧ ∃p (MechanicalEnergyOutputProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)) ∧ ∃f (PowerTransmissionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000346"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2322"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type based on positional role within mechanical systems. Under OWA, sufficient conditions would be difficult to specify without risk of misclassifying intermediate shafts or complex multi-shaft arrangements that happen to have output characteristics.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;OUTPUT SHAFT&gt; is a &lt;SHAFT&gt; that is the exit of mechanical energy and driver of an external energy consumer.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every output shaft is a shaft that participates in at least one mechanical energy output process and bears a power transmission function.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">eixo de saída</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">output shaft</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/AlternatingElectricalCurrent">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">corrente alternado elétrico</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">alternating electrical current</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1577">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FluidTransportProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000352">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A steel frame on which portable equipment is mounted to facilitate handling with cranes or flatbed trucks.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A 'support' intended to support items when being manufactured, transported, handled or installed.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] Move a well to a close-by locations with minimum rig down of equipment.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SKID&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;SUPPORT&gt; intended to support items when being manufactured, transported, handled or installed</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">skid</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">skid</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every skid is an assembly that bears an equipment support function and has a support frame and mounting points as component parts at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A skid is an assembly that bears an equipment support function, consisting of a support frame and mounting points, designed to support equipment items during manufacturing, transportation, handling, and installation.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um skid é uma montagem que possui uma função de suporte de equipamento, consistindo de uma estrutura de suporte e pontos de montagem, projetada para suportar itens de equipamento durante fabricação, transporte, manuseio e instalação.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b3000"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Skid(x) ↔ (Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(EquipmentSupportFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃s(SupportFrame(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)) ∧ ∃m(MountingPoint(m) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,m))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000369">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A distillation column intended to withstand outside pressure.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;VACUUM COLUMN&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;DISTILLATION COLUMN&gt; intended to withstand outside pressure</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A distillation column intended to withstand outside pressure</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma coluna de vácuo é uma coluna de destilação projetada para resistir à pressão externa durante operação sob vácuo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A vacuum column is a distillation column that is designed to withstand outside pressure during vacuum operation.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000255"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b3350"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b3351"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b3349"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">vacuum column</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">coluna de vácuo</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type based on structural capability. Under OWA, defining sufficient conditions for vacuum-capable design would be complex and could lead to false positives. The structural differentia (vacuum resistance) requires domain expert validation of what constitutes adequate vacuum design capability.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(VacuumColumn(x) → DistillationColumn(x) ∧ ∃q(VacuumPressureResistanceQuality(q) ∧ bearerOf(x,q)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every vacuum column is a distillation column that bears a vacuum pressure resistance quality.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000249">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A reciprocating pump intended to pump a liquid with a small capacity. This is done by means of thin flexible diaphragms to seal pumped fluid from leakage to atmosphere.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DIAPHRAGM PUMP&gt; is a &lt;RECIPROCATING PUMP&gt; intended to pump a liquid with a small capacity. This is done by means of thin flexible diaphragms to seal pumped fluid from leakage to atmosphere; flow rate is achieved through reciprocatory motion of the diaphragm</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bomba de diafragma</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">diaphragm pump</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(DiaphragmPump(x) → (ReciprocatingPump(x) ∧ ∃d(FlexibleDiaphragm(d) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,d)) ∧ ∃p(DiaphragmSealing(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma bomba de diafragma é uma bomba alternativa que usa diafragmas flexíveis para deslocar líquido e selar o fluido bombeado contra vazamento atmosférico.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A diaphragm pump is a reciprocating pump that uses flexible diaphragms to displace liquid and seal the pumped fluid from atmospheric leakage.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b936"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b937"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b938"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000337"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every diaphragm pump is a reciprocating pump that has flexible diaphragm as component part at all times and participates in diaphragm sealing.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions because this is a constructive type defined by physical mechanism. Under OWA, any pump with a flexible diaphragm component could be classified as a diaphragm pump, but there may be hybrid or specialized equipment containing diaphragms that should not be automatically classified into this maintenance category.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/LevelDetectionProcess">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">level detection process</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de detecção de nível</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000337">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">reciprocating pump</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bomba alternativa</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every reciprocating pump is a pump that has as component part at all times a reciprocating displacement mechanism and has as component part at all times pistons or plungers and has as component part at all times cylindrical chambers.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions for this constructive type. Under Open World Assumption, asserting equivalence based on structural differentia could lead to false positives where complex equipment containing reciprocating elements (like reciprocating compressors with auxiliary pumps, or hybrid systems) might be incorrectly classified as standard reciprocating pumps. The structural mechanism is necessary but sufficient conditions require domain expert validation.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2707"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000072"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2710"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2705"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2709"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2706"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2708"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A positive displacement pump which contains a displacing element intended to be moved in a reciprocating movement to exert pressure on a fluid, typically moving within a cylindrical space.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A type of fluid pump in which reciprocating pistons or plungers displace the fluid.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A piston pump.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;RECIPROCATING PUMP&gt; is a &lt;POSITIVE DISPLACEMENT PUMP&gt; which contains a displacing element intended to be moved in a reciprocating movement to exert pressure on a fluid, typically moving within a cylindrical space.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] a positive displacement pump which contains a displacing element intended to be moved in a reciprocating movement to exert pressure on a fluid, typically moving within a cylindrical space.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A reciprocating pump is a pump that contains pistons or plungers designed to move in a reciprocating motion within cylindrical chambers to displace fluid through positive displacement action.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma bomba alternativa é uma bomba que contém pistões ou êmbolos projetados para se moverem em movimento alternativo dentro de câmaras cilíndricas para deslocar fluido através de ação de deslocamento positivo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(ReciprocatingPump(x) → Pump(x) ∧ ∃m(ReciprocatingDisplacementMechanism(m) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,m)) ∧ ∃p(PistonOrPlunger(p) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p)) ∧ ∃c(CylindricalChamber(c) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,c)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b833">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/InletConnection"/>
  </rdf:Description>
