  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000267">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">FilterElement SubClassOf Filter and (madeFrom some FilterMedia) and (componentPartOf some FilterAssembly)</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification based on material composition (filter media) and mereological relationship (component of assembly). Under OWA, asserting equivalence could lead to unintended classification of any artifact made from filter media as a filter element, including specialized or hybrid components that contain filter media but serve different primary functions.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FILTER ELEMENT&gt; is a &lt;FILTER&gt; and that is the part of a filter assembly that is made from filter media</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1312"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000081"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um Filtro que é feito de meio filtrante e que é uma parte componente de um conjunto de filtro.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A Filter that is made from filter media and that is a component part of a filter assembly.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">elemento filtrante</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">filter element</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(FilterElement(x) → Filter(x) ∧ ∃m(FilterMedia(m) ∧ madeFrom(x,m)) ∧ ∃a(FilterAssembly(a) ∧ componentPartOf(x,a)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ThreePhaseSeparationProcess">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SeparationProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de separação trifásica</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">three phase separation process</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2010">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/InjectionPort"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000301">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A cone shaped device for separating fluids and the solids dispersed in fluids.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] An item of solids-control equipment consisting of an inverted cone, the mud being fed tangentially into the upper (larger diameter) part.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;HYDROCYCLONE&gt; is a &lt;CYCLONE&gt; and a &lt;CYLINDRICAL VESSEL&gt;, intended to separate a fluid by hydraulic forces</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">hydrocyclone</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">hidrociclone</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1935"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Hydrocyclone(x) ↔ Separator(x) ∧ ∃c(ConicalSection(c) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,c)) ∧ ∃p(CentrifugalSeparationProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um hidrociclone é um separador que separa misturas de fluidos usando forças centrífugas geradas por fluxo tangencial através de uma câmara cônica.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A hydrocyclone is a separator that separates fluid mixtures using centrifugal forces generated by tangential flow through a conical chamber.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every hydrocyclone is a separator that has a conical section as component part at all times and participates in centrifugal separation processes.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SuppressedDisturbance">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">suppressed disturbance</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">perturbação suprimido</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1687">
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1684"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#nil"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000271">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">arrestador de chama</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flame arrestor</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(FlameArrestor(x) ↔ SafetyDevice(x) ∧ ∃f(FlameArrestFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FLAME ARRESTOR&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and an &lt;ARRESTOR&gt; that is a trap covering an opening, e.g of a ventilation system or a pipe, to prevent flames from entering the system</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An arrestor which is a trap over an opening, e.g. of a ventilation system or a pipe, to prevent flames from entering the system.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every flame arrestor is a safety device that has the function of arresting flames and processes gaseous portions while preventing flame propagation.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A flame arrestor is a safety device that bears a flame arrest function to prevent flames from entering a system through an opening.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um arrestador de chama é um dispositivo de segurança que possui uma função de arrestar chama para prevenir que chamas entrem em um sistema através de uma abertura.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1362"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/EnclosureFunction">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1860"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1718"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1719"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b614"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b400"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b615"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b3245"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2694"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1772"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b426"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b399"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b469"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1773"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1859"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b427"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b3244"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2693"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b470"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">enclosure function</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de proteção e invólucro</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in an EnclosureProcess and that consists in providing a structural boundary that houses and protects internal mechanical components from the environment while maintaining structural integrity.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in an EnclosureProcess and that consists in providing a protective housing or containment boundary for internal components or mechanisms.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in an EnclosureProcess and that consists in providing a protective boundary around internal components while maintaining structural integrity and enabling controlled fluid flow through integral connection points.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in an EnclosureProcess and that consists in providing physical containment and environmental protection for internal components or systems.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in an EnclosureProcess and that consists in providing a protective boundary that contains, supports, and isolates internal components from external environment while maintaining structural integrity.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in an EnclosureProcess and that consists in providing protective containment and structural support for internal mechanical components, maintaining their spatial arrangement and protecting them from external environmental conditions.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in an EnclosureProcess and that consists in providing a structural boundary that contains and directs fluid flow while accommodating internal flow control components.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in an EnclosureProcess and that consists in providing a protective boundary that separates an internal space from the external environment while providing structural support for contained components.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/Shell">
