  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ElectricalConductionFunction">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in an ElectricalConductionProcess and that consists in providing a conductive pathway for electrical current within an electrical contact assembly.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in an ElectricalConductionProcess and that consists in providing a pathway for electrical current to pass from one electrical apparatus to another, enabling electrical connectivity and power or signal transmission.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1200"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1199"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b3083"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b3084"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">electrical conduction function</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de condução elétrica</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000216">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A funnel shaped pipe at the top of the casing that guides tool string entry and may have a side port for fluid pumping.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] An enlarged pipe at the top of a casing string that serves as a funnel to guide drilling tools into the top of a well.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A Bell nipple is a section of large diameter pipe fitted to the top of the blowout preventers that the flow line attaches to via a side outlet, to allow the drilling fluid to flow back over the shale shakers to the mud tanks. Also an enlarged pipe at the top of a casing string that serves as a funnel to guide drilling tools into the top of a well.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;BELL NIPPLE&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a large diameter &lt;PIPING NETWORK SEGMENT&gt; fitted to the top of the blowout preventers that the flow line attaches to via a side outlet, to allow the drilling fluid to flow back over the shale shakers to the mud tanks. Also an enlarged pipe at the top of a casing string that serves as a funnel to guide drilling tools into the top of a well</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">bell nipple</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bell nipple</rdfs:label>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000216"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um bell nipple é um tubo que conduz fluidos de perfuração em operações de perfuração e é caracterizado por um diâmetro alargado que serve como funil e uma localização no conjunto da cabeça do poço.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A bell nipple is a pipe that conducts drilling fluids in drilling operations and is characterized by an enlarged diameter that serves as a funnel and a location at the wellhead assembly.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b235"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(BellNipple(x) ↔ (Pipe(x) ∧ ∃f(DrillingFluidConductionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃s(EnlargedDiameter(s) ∧ hasCharacteristicShape(x,s)) ∧ ∃l(WellheadAssembly(l) ∧ hasLocation(x,l))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every bell nipple is a pipe that bears a DrillingFluidConductionFunction and has an enlarged diameter shape and is located at a wellhead assembly.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000327">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um atuador pneumático é um atuador que opera usando energia pneumática.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A pneumatic actuator is an actuator that operates using pneumatic power.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000207"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2504"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2503"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2501"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2502"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type where pneumatic mechanism is necessary but may not be sufficient under OWA. Specialized pneumatic equipment (pneumatic tools, pneumatic cylinders) might have pneumatic power but should not be classified as actuators without additional validation of their actuation role in control systems.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(PneumaticActuator(x) → Actuator(x) ∧ ∃y(PneumaticPower(y) ∧ hasOperatingMedium(x,y)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pneumatic actuator</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">atuador pneumático</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PNEUMATIC ACTUATOR&gt; is an &lt;INSTRUMENTATION ITEM&gt; and a &lt;CONTROLLED ACTUATOR&gt; that is intended to be operated by pneumatic power</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] An actuator that is intended to be operated by pneumatic power.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An actuator that is intended to be operated by pneumatic power.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every pneumatic actuator is an actuator that has operating medium some pneumatic power.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
