  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000372">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An Assembly that bears a ForceTransmissionFunction and that has a valve stem seal as a component part, specifically designed to transmit motion from a valve operator to the valve closure member.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um Assembly que porta uma ForceTransmissionFunction e que tem um selo de haste de válvula como parte componente, especificamente projetado para transmitir movimento de um operador de válvula para o membro de fechamento da válvula.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b3388"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b3389"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type defined by physical structure (rod/shaft mechanism). Under Open World Assumption, sufficient conditions would force any assembly with a valve stem seal and force transmission function to be classified as a valve stem, which could include complex multi-component assemblies, manifolds, or specialized valve mechanisms that contain these elements but should not be asserted into the standard valve stem maintenance category.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">valve stem</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">haste de válvula</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">ValveStem SubClassOf Assembly and bearerOf some ForceTransmissionFunction and hasComponentPartAtAllTimes some ValveStemSeal</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(ValveStem(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(ForceTransmissionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃s(ValveStemSeal(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;VALVE STEM&gt; is a &lt;VALVE COMPONENT&gt; and a &lt;TRANSMITTER(force)&gt; that is a rod or shaft which is transmitting motion from an operator to the closure member of a valve</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
