  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000375">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ppdm] A Well is a permitted or actual drilled hole in the ground designed to exchange (or facilitate the exchange of) fluids between a subsurface reservoir and the surface (or another reservoir), or to enable the detection and measurement of rock properties. Key concept: A physical Well is created each time the drill bit breaks the surface of the earth. Clarification: A Well is the parent of the Wellhead Stream(s), Well Origin, and all Well Components down hole from its Well Origin. A Well has a single Well Origin and all Wellbore(s) that extend from this Well Origin are parts of the Well. Re-entry through the same Well Origin for a Well that has not been plugged and abandoned does not create a new Well. A Well that has the same geographic coordinates as a previously existing plugged and abandoned, reclaimed or undrilled Well is a new Well. WB2-Cl2 Diagram Note: The Well depicted on page 3 groups multiple Well Components, including: one active Well WB2-C1 Origin (WO1), one inactive Wellbore (WB1), two active Wellbores (WB2, WB3), three inactive Wellbore Completions (WB1-C1, WB1-C2, WB1-C3) and three active Wellbore Completions (WB2-C1, WB3-C1, WB3-C2) and two active Wellbore Contact Intervals (WB2- CI1, WB2-CI2). ® Copyright 2014, PPDM Association. All Rights Reserved PAGE 4</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;WELL&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that is arranged to obtain or produce from, or store or inject a material into, the earth</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A well is a collection of (zero or more) holes drilled into the Earth for the purpose of either (1) finding or producing underground resources; or (2) providing services related to the production of underground resources.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b3448"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um poço é um sistema projetado que interage com recursos do subsolo através de um furo perfurado, projetado para obter, produzir, armazenar ou injetar materiais na terra ou a partir dela.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A well is an engineered system that interacts with subsurface resources through a drilled wellbore, designed to obtain, produce, store, or inject materials into or from the earth.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Well(x) ↔ EngineeredSystem(x) ∧ ∃f(SubsurfaceResourceInteractionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃w(Wellbore(w) ∧ hasComponentPartAtSomeTime(x,w)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">well</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">poço</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every well is an engineered system that bears a subsurface resource interaction function and has a wellbore as component part.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000212">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Anode(x) ↔ ElectricalEquipment(x) ∧ ∃f(AnodeFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b120"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">ânodo</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">anode</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] The positively charged site in a cell. Oxidation site. The site of metal loss in corrosion.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;ANODE&gt; is an &lt;ELECTRICAL DEVICE&gt; that has a capability of &lt;EMITTING&gt; positive charge carriers to, and/or &lt;RECEIVING&gt; negative charge carriers from, the medium of lower conductivity</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that is capable of emitting positive charge carriers to and/or receiving negative charge carriers from the medium of lower conductivity.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] The half of a battery that is positively charged and to which anions migrate by electrostatic attraction.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An anode is electrical equipment that bears the function of serving as the positive electrode in electrochemical processes, capable of emitting positive charge carriers to and/or receiving negative charge carriers from a medium of lower conductivity.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um ânodo é um equipamento elétrico que possui a função de servir como eletrodo positivo em processos eletroquímicos, capaz de emitir portadores de carga positiva para e/ou receber portadores de carga negativa de um meio de menor condutividade.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every anode is electrical equipment that has the function of electrochemical oxidation and has electrical connection and active material as component parts at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FluidPort">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">fluid port</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bocal de fluido</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/WellFluid">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">well fluid</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">fluido de poço</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000349">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">sheave</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">polia</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2947"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2946"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2948"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Sheave(x) → MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃y(GroovedRim(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)) ∧ ∃f(PowerTransmissionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A grooved pulley.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] In oilfield usage, the term usually refers to either the pulleys permanently mounted on the top of the rig (the crown blocks), or the pulleys used for running wireline tools into the wellbore.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SHEAVE&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;WHEEL&gt; which is grooved for use with vee-belts, ropes, round belts, wire or pipe</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A wheel which is grooved for use with vee-belts, ropes, round belts, wire or pipe.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type based on physical structure. Under OWA, defining sufficient conditions based solely on having a grooved rim could lead to false positives where other grooved mechanical elements (like timing belt pulleys with different design intents) are automatically classified as sheaves. The structural differentia provides necessary conditions while allowing domain experts to confirm sufficient conditions.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma polia é um artefato material que é uma roda sulcada projetada para transmitir energia mecânica através da interface com correias, cordas, cabos ou tubos.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A sheave is a material artifact that is a grooved wheel designed to transmit mechanical power through interface with belts, ropes, wires, or pipes.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every sheave is a material artifact that has a grooved rim as component part and bears a power transmission function.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FiltrationProcess">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which particles, contaminants, or unwanted substances are selectively retained from a fluid stream by a filter element through mechanical screening or other separation mechanisms while clean fluid passes through.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">filtration process</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de filtração</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1655">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/CylinderBlock"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1067">
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1068"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1060"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/EnclosureProcess">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a housing artifact creates and maintains a protective boundary around internal components, simultaneously providing structural support and environmental separation.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a housing or casing provides containment and protection for internal components, maintaining separation between the internal mechanism and external environment.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a body or housing artifact provides structural containment and protection for internal mechanical components or assemblies.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a structural housing provides containment and protection for mechanical components, creating a defined boundary between internal mechanisms and the external environment.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a casing provides protective containment around mechanical components while enabling controlled fluid passage through designed openings and maintaining pressure boundaries.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a structural body provides containment and directional guidance for fluid flow while housing internal valve components that control the flow.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a housing structure provides physical containment and environmental protection for internal components, shielding them from external conditions such as moisture, dust, mechanical impact, and temperature variations.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a casing provides protective containment around internal components, maintaining their operational environment and structural integrity while allowing controlled access for maintenance.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de proteção e invólucro</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">enclosure process</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/InterfacingProcess">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de interfaceamento</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">interfacing process</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a port establishes and maintains a point of interface that enables communication, connection, or interaction between distinct objects or systems.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000250">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">DieselEngine(x) → Engine(x) ∧ ∃s(CompressionIgnitionSystem(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)) ∧ ∃f(FuelInjectionSystem(f) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,f)) ∧ ∃p(CompressionIgnitionProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">motor diesel</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">diesel engine</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions for this constructive type. While compression ignition is characteristic of diesel engines, under OWA we cannot be certain that any engine with compression ignition systems is necessarily a diesel engine - there could be hybrid or specialized engines with similar mechanisms that should not be auto-classified as standard diesel engines without expert validation.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b975"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b974"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b976"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b977"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000264"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b973"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A diesel engine is an engine that ignites fuel through compression heat rather than spark ignition, requiring compression ignition and fuel injection systems.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um motor diesel é um motor que inflama combustível através do calor de compressão em vez de ignição por centelha, requerendo sistemas de ignição por compressão e injeção de combustível.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An internal combustion engine in which ignition of the fuel injected into the cylinder is performed by the heat of compression of the air charge.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DIESEL ENGINE&gt; is  an &lt;INTERNAL COMBUSTION ENGINE&gt; and a &lt;RECIPROCATING PISTON ENGINE&gt; in which ignition of the fuel injected into the cylinder is performed by the heat of compression of the air charge</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] An internal combustion engine in which ignition of the fuel injected into the cylinder is performed by the heat of compression of the air charge.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">A diesel engine is necessarily an engine that has compression ignition system and fuel injection system and participates in compression ignition process.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PhysicalObject">
