  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000221">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A unit or assembly of units or sections and associated fittings forming a rigid structural system used to securely fasten or support cables and raceways.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] An artefact and electrical cable conduit consisting of a continuous base, raised edges and no covering</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every cable tray is an assembly that has the function to support cables and has a continuous base part and raised edge parts.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A cable tray is an assembly that bears a cable support function and consists of a continuous base with raised edges, forming a rigid structural system for securely supporting and routing electrical cables.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma bandeja de cabos é um conjunto que possui função de suporte de cabos e consiste em uma base contínua com bordas elevadas, formando um sistema estrutural rígido para suportar e rotear cabos elétricos de forma segura.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(CableTray(x) ↔ Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(CableSupportFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃b(ContinuousBase(b) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,b)) ∧ ∃e(RaisedEdge(e) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,e)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">cable tray</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bandeja de cabos</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b388"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2668">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PressureContainmentProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000246">
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b893"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DETECTOR&gt; is an &lt;INSTRUMENTATION FUNCTION&gt; that has a capability of &lt;DETECTING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[isa5_1] a device that is used to detect the presence of something, such as flammable or toxic gases or discrete parts; see also primary element and sensor.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that is an assembly of a sensing element and necessary ancillary devices making it able of detecting a state, e.g. pressure, temperature, or detect the presence of a selected substance, and produce a signal based on the detection.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A sensor or receiver, such as a geophone or hydrophone, gravimeter or magnetometer.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A detector is an instrument that bears a detection function, enabling it to sense states, substances, or phenomena and produce signals based on the detection.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um detector é um instrumento que possui uma função de detecção, permitindo-lhe detectar estados, substâncias ou fenômenos e produzir sinais baseados na detecção.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every detector is an instrument that has a detection function and has component parts including a sensing element and signal generation device.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Detector(x) ↔ Instrument(x) ∧ ∃f(DetectionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">detector</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">detector</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/TemperatureMeasurementFunction">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
