  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/IntakeValve">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">intake valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula de admissão</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000077"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000227">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000370"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b476"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ClosureMember"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every check valve closure member is a MaterialArtifact that is component part of some check valve and bears some BackflowPreventionFunction</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">check valve closure member</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">membro de fechamento de válvula de retenção</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CHECK VALVE CLOSURE MEMBER&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;VALVE CLOSURE MEMBER&gt; that is intended to prevent back flow</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A MaterialArtifact that is a component part of a check valve and that bears a BackflowPreventionFunction, consisting in a mechanical element that prevents fluid flow reversal by physically blocking the flow path when pressure conditions indicate potential backflow.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um MaterialArtifact que é uma parte componente de uma válvula de retenção e que possui uma BackflowPreventionFunction, consistindo em um elemento mecânico que previne o refluxo de fluido bloqueando fisicamente o caminho de fluxo quando as condições de pressão indicam potencial refluxo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(CheckValveClosureMember(x) → MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃y(CheckValve(y) ∧ isComponentPartOf(x,y)) ∧ ∃f(BackflowPreventionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type defined by structural role and mechanism. Under OWA, sufficient conditions would force classification of any artifact with backflow prevention function and check valve association, potentially including hybrid or specialized designs that should not be automatically classified as standard closure members without domain expert validation.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b977">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/Piston"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1000">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/DifferentialPressureSwitchingProcess"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000229">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every chromatograph is a process analyzer that has the function of chromatographic analysis.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A chromatograph is a process analyzer that bears a chromatographic analysis function.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um cromatógrafo é um analisador de processo que possui uma função de análise cromatográfica.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An analysing instrument that applies the principle of chromatography to analyse the molecular composition of a substance.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CHROMATOGRAPH&gt; is a &lt;PROCESS ANALYSER&gt; that analyses the molecular composition of a substance</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">chromatograph</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">cromatógrafo</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Chromatograph(x) ↔ ProcessAnalyzer(x) ∧ ∃f (ChromatographicAnalysisFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b531"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b710">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/CoolingProcess"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SealingProcess">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de vedação</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">sealing process</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a valve seat provides a sealing interface for a closure element (gate, ball, disc) to bear against, preventing fluid passage when the valve is closed.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ContainmentProcess">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a structural boundary maintains separation between internal contents and external environment, preventing uncontrolled release while withstanding internal pressure loads.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which material is enclosed and retained within a defined spatial boundary by a containing artifact.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a container artifact encloses and maintains internal components or fluids within its structural boundaries, providing physical separation from the external environment.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">containment process</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de contenção</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000276">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A tank or vessel in which a process stream is charged or pumped and where lighter products flash off or vaporize and are drawn off at the top. The remainder heavier fractions are drawn off at the bottom of the vessel.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FLASH DRUM&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;VESSEL&gt; in which a process stream is charged or pumped and where lighter products flash off or vaporize and are drawn off at the top. The remainer heavier fractions are drawn off at the bottom of the vessel</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A flash drum is a separator that performs flash vaporization to separate lighter components (which vaporize and are drawn off at the top) from heavier components (which remain liquid and are drawn off at the bottom).</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um tambor de flash é um separador que realiza vaporização flash para separar componentes mais leves (que vaporizam e são retirados no topo) de componentes mais pesados (que permanecem líquidos e são retirados no fundo).</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(FlashDrum(x) ↔ Separator(x) ∧ ∃f(FlashVaporizationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1458"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">tambor de flash</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flash drum</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every flash drum is a separator that bears a flash vaporization function and has a vapor outlet, liquid outlet, and feed inlet.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1725">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000066"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b471">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/EnclosureFunction"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
