  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000296">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1856"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1858"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000321"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1857"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1855"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A tubular which is flexible and capable of conveying liquids under pressure.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;HOSE&gt; is a &lt;TUBULAR&gt; that is flexible and capable of conducting liquids under pressure</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A tubular which is flexible and capable of conveying liquids under pressure.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every hose is a pipe that has flexibility and is capable of conducting liquids under pressure.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">mangueira</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">hose</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma mangueira é um tubo flexível projetado para conduzir líquidos sob pressão enquanto acomoda movimento posicional e flexão.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A hose is a flexible pipe designed to conduct liquids under pressure while accommodating positional movement and bending.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions because this is a constructive type defined by physical properties (flexibility). Under OWA, asserting equivalence would force any artifact with flexibility and pressure capability to be classified as a hose, potentially including complex equipment with flexible components that should not be categorized as standard hoses.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Hose(x) → Pipe(x) ∧ ∃q(Flexibility(q) ∧ hasQuality(x,q)) ∧ ∃c(PressurizedFluidConduction(c) ∧ capableOf(x,c)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ReciprocatingPistonMechanism">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">reciprocating piston mechanism</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">mecanismo alternativo de pistão</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PneumaticEnergyConversionProcess">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pneumatic energy conversion process</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de conversão de energia pneumática</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000302">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every impeller is an assembly that has rotating vanes and a hub as component parts at all times, participates in rotational motion, and bears an energy transfer function.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">impulsor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">impeller</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1954"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1955"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1956"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;IMPELLER&gt; is a &lt;MECHANICAL TO MECHANICAL ENERGY CONVERTER&gt; that is an assembly of rotating vanes within an enclosure which is used to impart energy to or derive energy from a fluid through dynamic force</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] In electromagnetics or electrical circuit theory, the ratio of voltage to current when these are represented by phasor quantities in alternating current circuits. (A phasor is a complex number that represents the amplitude and phase of a quantity that varies sinusoidally in time.) Electrical impedance, also symbolized by Z, is a complex number that has the same units (ohms) as resistivity.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] The rotating pump component that drives the fluid in a centrifugal pump.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[DEXPI] An energy converter component that is an assembly of rotating vanes within an enclosure which is used to impart energy to or derive energy from a fluid through dynamic force (from ``_).</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Impeller(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃v,h(RotatingVanes(v) ∧ Hub(h) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,v) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,h) ∧ ∃m(RotationalMotion(m) ∧ participatesIn(x,m)) ∧ ∃f(EnergyTransferFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An impeller is an assembly consisting of rotating vanes mounted on a hub that transfers energy to or from fluids through dynamic rotational force within an enclosure.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um impulsor é um conjunto que consiste em pás rotativas montadas em um cubo que transfere energia para ou de fluidos através de força rotacional dinâmica dentro de um invólucro.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification based on physical mechanism. Under OWA, defining sufficient conditions for the rotating vane assembly could lead to false positives where other rotating equipment with vanes (like turbine rotors or fan assemblies) might be incorrectly classified as impellers when they should remain in their specific equipment categories.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/AccumulationFunction">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">accumulation function</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de acumulação</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b19"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b18"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000288">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1720"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000222"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">GearCasing ⊑ casing ⊓ ∃hasContent.GearMechanism</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">carcaça de caixa de engrenagens</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gear casing</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(GearCasing(x) → casing(x) ∧ ∃y(GearMechanism(y) ∧ hasContent(x,y)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A casing that contains and houses the internal components of a gear mechanism, providing protective enclosure and structural support.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um invólucro que contém e abriga os componentes internos de um mecanismo de engrenagem, fornecendo invólucro protetor e suporte estrutural.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">This is a constructive type defined by its physical configuration as a specific type of casing. Under OWA, declaring equivalence could lead to over-classification where any casing containing gear-like components might be inappropriately classified as a standard gear casing, including custom enclosures or hybrid systems that should not fall into this maintenance category.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;GEAR CASING&gt; is a &lt;HOUSING&gt; that contains the internal components of a gear.</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2026">
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2027"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2021"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b3192">
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b3193"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000084"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000209">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">trocador de calor resfriado a ar</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">air cooled heat exchanger</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000092"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b82"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b81"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b80"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b83"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Under the Open World Assumption, defining air cooling constructively as sufficient conditions could lead to false positives. Complex hybrid equipment or specialized configurations with air cooling components might be inappropriately classified. Starting with necessary conditions allows for proper validation by domain experts before upgrading to equivalence.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An air cooled heat exchanger is a heat exchanger that has finned air cooling surfaces and uses ambient air as the cooling medium to transfer thermal energy from process fluids.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um trocador de calor resfriado a ar é um trocador de calor que possui superfícies aletadas de resfriamento a ar e usa ar ambiente como meio de resfriamento para transferir energia térmica de fluidos de processo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A cooler that is intended to use air as the cooling medium.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A cooler that is intended to use air as the cooling medium.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;AIR COOLED HEAT EXCHANGER&gt; is a &lt;HEAT EXCHANGER&gt; and an &lt;AIR COOLED OBJECT&gt; and a &lt;FLUID CONTAINER&gt;</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(AirCooledHeatExchanger(x) → HeatExchanger(x) ∧ ∃y(AirFinSystem(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)) ∧ ∃z(TubeBundle(z) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,z)) ∧ ∃p(AirCoolingProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every air cooled heat exchanger is a heat exchanger that has component parts including an air fin system and tube bundle, and participates in air cooling processes.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b724">
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b725"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b718"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b3208">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ConversionElement"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b674">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ControlProcess"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000218">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] The equipment or tools at the bottom of the tubing or drill string. The BHA is changed to achieve a certain result.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;BOTTOM HOLE ASSEMBLY&gt; is a &lt;DRILLING COMPONENT&gt; that is the lower part of a drill string, extending from the bit to the drill pipe.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b316"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A bottom hole assembly is a drilling component that performs specialized drilling operations at the bottom of the drill string, characterized by including a drill bit and being positioned at the bottom hole location.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um conjunto de fundo de poço é um componente de perfuração que realiza operações especializadas de perfuração na parte inferior da coluna de perfuração, caracterizado por incluir uma broca e estar posicionado no local do fundo do poço.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every bottom hole assembly is a drilling component that has a drill bit as component part at all times and is located at bottom hole location.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">bottom hole assembly</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">conjunto de fundo de poço</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(BottomHoleAssembly(x) ↔ DrillingComponent(x) ∧ ∃y(DrillBit(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)) ∧ ∃z(BottomHoleLocation(z) ∧ locatedAt(x,z)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1629">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/CyclonicFlowChamber"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000362">
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b3205"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Transducer(x) ↔ Instrument(x) ∧ ∃f (TransductionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every transducer is an instrument that has the designed function to convert energy or signal forms while preserving information content.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">transducer</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">transdutor</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A transducer is an instrument that bears a TransductionFunction to convert information from one form or magnitude of energy to another form or magnitude.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um transdutor é um instrumento que possui uma FunçãoDeTransdução para converter informação de uma forma ou magnitude de energia para outra forma ou magnitude.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;TRANSDUCER&gt; is an &lt;ENERGY CONVERTER&gt; that is capable of converting a &lt;PROCESS VARIABLE&gt; in one form or magnitude of energy to another form or magnitude of the same energy</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[isa5_1] a general term for a device, which can be a primary element, transmitter, relay, converter or other device, that receives information in the form of one or more physical quantities, modifies the information or its form, or both if required, and produces a resultant output signal.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] An artefact that accepts information in the form of a physical or chemical variable (its input variable) and converts it into an output variable of the same or another nature, according to a definite law.</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ChromatographicAnalysisProcess">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de análise cromatográfica</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">chromatographic analysis process</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FuseBase">
