    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">high pressure signal</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b808">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/DehumidificationProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2801">
    <rdf:rest rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#nil"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2797"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000237">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions for this constructive type. Under the Open World Assumption, defining sufficient conditions based on Coriolis principle usage could lead to false positives where other devices using Coriolis forces (like gyroscopes or accelerometers) might be incorrectly classified as flow meters. The structural differentia provides necessary conditions that can be validated by domain experts.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(CoriolisMassFlowMeter(x) → FlowMeter(x) ∧ ∃y(CoriolisFlowTube(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)) ∧ ∃z(CoriolisPrinciple(z) ∧ utilizesPhysicalPrinciple(x,z)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um medidor de vazão que utiliza o princípio de Coriolis através de tubos de fluxo oscilantes especializados para medir diretamente a vazão mássica de fluidos.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A flow meter that utilizes the Coriolis principle through specialized oscillating flow tubes to directly measure mass flow rate of fluids.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every coriolis mass flow meter is a flow meter that has component part at all times some Coriolis flow tube and utilizes the Coriolis principle.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">coriolis mass flow meter</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">medidor de vazão Coriolis</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b742"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b738"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b741"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b740"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000278"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b739"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A mass flow meter that uses the Coriolis principle to measure a mass flow rate through the meter.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A mass flow meter that uses the Coriolis principle to measure a mass flow rate through the meter.</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000355">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;STATOR&gt; is a &lt;MACHINE COMPONENT&gt; that is the arrangement of primary coils being the stator winding and being the stationary part of a machine</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] In the context of a PDM motor, a stator is the stationary rubber element of a PDM motor.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">stator</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">MaterialArtifact que possui uma StationaryMachineComponentFunction e</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every Stator is a MaterialArtifact that bears a StationaryMachineComponentFunction and is part of some RotatingMachine</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um MaterialArtifact que possui uma StationaryMachineComponentFunction e que é o componente estrutural estacionário dentro de máquinas rotativas, fornecendo alojamento e estabilidade posicional para elementos ativos como bobinas, palhetas ou vedações.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A MaterialArtifact that bears a StationaryMachineComponentFunction and that is the stationary structural component within rotating machinery, providing housing and positional stability for active elements such as windings, vanes, or seals.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b3046"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b3047"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Stator(x) → MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃f(StationaryMachineComponentFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃m(RotatingMachine(m) ∧ partOf(x,m)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification based on structural positioning within rotating machinery. Under OWA, any artifact described as stationary within a rotating machine context could be classified as a stator, but this may include specialized hybrid components, mounting structures, or custom configurations that should not be automatically asserted into the standard stator maintenance category. The structural differentia (stationary positioning) is necessary but making it sufficient requires domain expert validation.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2920">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ShakingFunction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b3025">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SpacingProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1477">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FluidConductionProcess"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000234">
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b679"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A controller is an instrument that bears a control function, automatically regulating a controlled variable by measuring it, comparing with a reference value, and generating output signals to reduce deviation.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um controlador é um instrumento que possui uma função de controle, regulando automaticamente uma variável controlada ao medi-la, comparar com um valor de referência e gerar sinais de saída para reduzir o desvio.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">controlador</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">controller</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[isa5_1] a device having an output that varies to regulate a controlled variable in a specified manner that may be a self-contained analog or digital instrument, or may be the equivalent of such an instrument in a shared- control system.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A regulator that operates automatically to affect a controlled variable by comparing the value of the controlled variable with the value of a reference variable in order to reduce the difference between them.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A device that measures a controlled variable, compares it with a predetermined setting and signals an actuator to readjust the opening of a valve.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CONTROLLER&gt; is an &lt;INSTRUMENTATION FUNCTION&gt; that is capable of &lt;CONTROLLING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every controller is an instrument that has the function to control a process variable by automatic feedback regulation</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Controller(x) ↔ Instrument(x) ∧ ∃f(ControlFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SolidBulkStorageFunction">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2985"/>
