  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000340">
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type based on rotary motion mechanism. Under OWA, providing sufficient conditions could lead to over-classification where any equipment that happens to produce rotary motion (motors, turbines, etc.) might be incorrectly classified as rotary actuators. The rotary motion differentia is necessary but requires domain expert validation to confirm it is sufficient for the actuator equipment category.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um atuador rotativo é um atuador que causa movimento rotativo convertendo sinais de controle em saída mecânica rotacional controlada.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A rotary actuator is an actuator that causes rotary motion by converting control signals into controlled rotational mechanical output.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000207"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2773"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">rotary actuator</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">atuador rotativo</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (RotaryActuator(x) → Actuator(x) ∧ ∃p (RotaryMotionProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every rotary actuator is an actuator that participates in rotary motion processes.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;ROTARY ACTUATOR&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and an &lt;ACTUATOR&gt; causing a rotary motion</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b3046">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/StationaryMachineComponentFunction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000368">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every UPS unit is electrical equipment that has the function of maintaining uninterrupted AC electric power supply.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A UPS unit is electrical equipment that bears the designed function of maintaining uninterrupted AC electric power supply to protected equipment during power disturbances.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma unidade UPS é um equipamento elétrico que possui a função projetada de manter o fornecimento ininterrupto de energia elétrica AC para equipamentos protegidos durante distúrbios de energia.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;UPS UNIT&gt; is an &lt;AC ELECTRIC POWER SUPPLY UNIT&gt; that maintains a uninterrupted supply of electric power to the equipment it protects</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] An A.C. power supply unit that maintains a continuous supply of electric power to the equipment it protects.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An ac power supply unit that maintains a continuous supply of electric power to the equipment it protects.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">ups unit</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">unidade UPS</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b3328"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(UPSUnit(x) ↔ ElectricalEquipment(x) ∧ ∃f(UninterruptedPowerSupplyFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2728">
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2724"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#nil"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000345">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">scrubber</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">lavador de gases</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A device to remove dirt, water, foreign matter, or undesired liquids that are part of the gas flowstream.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A reactor that removes various components from produced gas.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A distillation column intended to clean gas by washing the gas flow with water or with another liquid entering at the top of the vessel and sprayed in the gas. Typically to remove dust and small particles.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A distillation column intended to clean gas by washing the gas flow with water or with another liquid entering at the top of the vessel and sprayed in the gas. Typically to remove dust and small particles.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SCRUBBER&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;SEPARATOR&gt; intended to clean gas by washing the gas flow with water or with another liquid entering at the top of the vessel and sprayed in the gas. Typically to remove dust and small particles</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every scrubber is a separator that has the function of separation and participates in liquid washing processes with both gas and liquid inputs.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2855"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A scrubber is a separator that cleans gas by washing the gas flow with liquid to remove contaminants such as dust, particles, or undesired substances.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um lavador de gases é um separador que limpa gás através da lavagem do fluxo gasoso com líquido para remover contaminantes como poeira, partículas ou substâncias indesejadas.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Scrubber(x) ↔ Separator(x) ∧ ∃f,p,g,l (SeparationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f) ∧ LiquidWashingProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p) ∧ GasPortion(g) ∧ LiquidPortion(l) ∧ hasInput(x,g) ∧ hasInput(x,l)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PigLaunchingFunction">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de lançamento de pig</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pig launching function</rdfs:label>
