  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000263">
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1211"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">conector elétrico</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">electrical connector</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(ElectricalConnector(x) ↔ ElectricalEquipment(x) ∧ ∃f(ElectricalConnectionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A connector for holding two parts of a conductor in intimate contact.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;ELECTRICAL CONNECTOR&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and an &lt;CONNECTOR&gt; for holding two parts of &lt;ELECTRICAL CONDUCTOR&gt; in intimate contact</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um conector elétrico é um equipamento elétrico que possui uma função de conexão elétrica e que mantém contato elétrico íntimo entre duas ou mais partes de condutor elétrico para permitir fluxo contínuo de corrente.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An electrical connector is an electrical equipment that bears an electrical connection function and that maintains intimate electrical contact between two or more electrical conductor parts to enable continuous current flow.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">ElectricalConnector ≡ ElectricalEquipment ⊓ ∃bearerOf.ElectricalConnectionFunction</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000215">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um mancal é um artefato material que é projetado para suportar e localizar elementos mecânicos móveis ou estáticos enquanto reduz o atrito na conexão.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A bearing is a material artifact that is designed to support and locate moving or static mechanical elements while reducing friction in the connection.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every bearing is a material artifact that bears a support function and participates in friction reduction processes</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Bearing(x) ↔ MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃f(SupportFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃p(FrictionReductionProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">mancal</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">bearing</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;BEARING&gt; is a &lt;SUPPORT&gt; intended to support and locate a moving or static element</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object intended to support and locate a moving or static element and capable of reducing friction and transfer forces in a connection.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b211"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/DivergingChannel">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">canal divergente</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">diverging channel</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000305">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">poço de injeção</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">injection well</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A well either specifically drilled, or, more likely, a poor producer that is converted to inject fluids to stabilize the decline of pressure in a productive zone. An injector is required to have a pressure connection to the pay and to a producing well. Water is typically injected at the base of the pay or, in a gas well, or gas is injected into the gas cap.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;INJECTION WELL&gt; is  a &lt;WELL&gt; with the purpose of injecting a material into a reservoir, normally with a pressure higher than the formation pressure</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A well in which fluids are injected rather than produced, the primary objective typically being to maintain reservoir pressure.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (InjectionWell(x) ↔ (Well(x) ∧ ∃f (InjectionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An injection well is a well that bears the designed function of injecting materials into a reservoir at pressure higher than formation pressure.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um poço de injeção é um poço que possui a função projetada de injetar materiais em um reservatório a uma pressão superior à pressão da formação.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2018"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every injection well is a well that has the function to inject materials into a reservoir under pressure.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FlameArrestFunction">
