  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000373">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">vessel head</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">tampo de vaso</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b3413"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(VesselHead(x) → FiatObjectPart(x) ∧ ∃y(Vessel(y) ∧ partOf(x,y)) ∧ ∃r(VesselClosureRole(r) ∧ realizes(x,r)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type based on structural configuration. Under OWA, asserting sufficient conditions for vessel head closure would inappropriately classify any part that closes a vessel (including specialized manifolds, complex multi-port heads, or custom closures) as standard vessel heads, potentially creating false positives in maintenance categorization.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every vessel head is a fiat object part that is part of some vessel and realizes a vessel closure role.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;VESSEL HEAD&gt; is an &lt;EQUIPMENT COMPONENT&gt; that is intended to close a vessel shell.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A FiatObjectPart that is part of a vessel and that closes a vessel shell by providing an end boundary for containment.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma FiatObjectPart que é parte de um vaso e que fecha o casco do vaso fornecendo uma fronteira terminal para contenção.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000228">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">árvore de natal</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">christmas tree</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CHRISTMAS TREE&gt; is a &lt;PIPING SYSTEM&gt; that is an assembly of pipes and piping parts, with valves and associated control equipment that is connected to the top of a wellhead and is intended for control of fluid from a well.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that is an assembly of pipes and piping parts, with valves and associated control equipment that is connected to the top of a wellhead and is intended for control of fluid from a well.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] The control sections that sits above the basic wellhead. It may contain hangers, master valves, annular valves, wing valves, and gauges or pressure, flow rate or monitoring measurement equipment.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] An 'artefact' that is an assembly of pipes and piping parts, with valves and associated control equipment that is connected to the top of a wellhead and is intended for control of fluid from a well.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] The set of valves, spools, and fittings connected to the top of a well to direct and control the flow of formation fluids from the well.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A christmas tree is an assembly that bears a well fluid control function, is connected to a wellhead, and contains master valves for controlling formation fluids from oil and gas wells.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma árvore de natal é um conjunto que possui uma função de controle de fluidos de poço, está conectada a uma cabeça de poço, e contém válvulas mestras para controlar fluidos de formação de poços de petróleo e gás.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (ChristmasTree(x) ↔ (Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(WellFluidControlFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃w(Wellhead(w) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,w)) ∧ ∃v(MasterValve(v) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,v))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every christmas tree is an assembly that has the function to control well fluids and is connected to a wellhead and has master valves as component parts.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000228"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b504"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000269">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A finned tube heat exchanger is a heat exchanger that has finned tubes as the primary heat transfer surface enhancement mechanism.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um trocador de calor de tubos aletados é um trocador de calor que possui tubos aletados como mecanismo primário de aumento da superfície de transferência de calor.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions for this constructive type. While finned tubes are the defining structural feature, making sufficient conditions (equivalence) under Open World Assumption could lead to false positives where any assembly containing finned tubes would be classified as this specific heat exchanger type, including complex multi-function equipment or specialized hybrid systems.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1335"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000092"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1332"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1334"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1333"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FINNED TUBE HEAT EXCHANGER&gt; is an &lt;INDIRECT CONTACT HEAT EXCHANGER&gt; that has finned tubes</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A heat exchanger that has finned tubes.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A heat exchange that has finned tubes.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(FinnedTubeHeatExchanger(x) → HeatExchanger(x) ∧ ∃y(FinnedTube(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every finned tube heat exchanger is a heat exchanger that has finned tubes as component parts at all times</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">trocador de calor de tubos aletados</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">finned tube heat exchanger</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/EquipmentSupportProcess">
