  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b345">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/CombustionFunction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000342">
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">As a constructive type defined by physical configuration (rotating portion with shaft), providing sufficient conditions under OWA could lead to overclassification. Complex assemblies containing rotating elements might be incorrectly classified as rotors rather than their proper categories (motors, compressors, etc.).</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2789"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">rotor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">rotor</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Rotor(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃p(RotationalMotionProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)) ∧ ∃s(RotorShaft(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] The rotating shaft in a PDM motor.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;ROTOR&gt; is a &lt;MACHINE COMPONENT&gt; that is the rotating portion of a machine</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An Assembly that participates in rotational motion and has a rotor shaft as an essential component, designed to transfer mechanical energy through rotational motion within a machine assembly.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um Assembly que participa em movimento rotacional e tem um eixo do rotor como componente essencial, projetado para transferir energia mecânica através de movimento rotacional dentro de um conjunto de máquina.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every Rotor is an Assembly that participates in some RotationalMotionProcess and has some rotor shaft as component part at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000356">
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b3087"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">switch contact</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">contato de chave</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A switch contact is an electrical contact that is one of the conductive parts forming a contact assembly.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um contato de chave é um contato elétrico que é uma das partes condutoras que formam um conjunto de contato.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SWITCH CONTACT&gt; is an &lt;ELECTRICAL CONTACT&gt; that is one of the conductive parts forming a contact.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (SwitchContact(x) → ElectricalContact(x) ∧ ∃y(ElectricalContact(y) ∧ partOf(x,y)) ∧ ∃f(ElectricalConductionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every switch contact is an electrical contact that is part of an electrical contact assembly and bears an electrical conduction function.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type based on structural role as a conductive part. Under OWA, asserting sufficient conditions could incorrectly classify any conductive part of an electrical contact as a switch contact, when there may be other specialized conductive components (bus bars, terminals, etc.) that serve different structural roles.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/MechanicalMotion">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">mechanical motion</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">movimento mecânico</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000367">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um umbilical é uma montagem que é um feixe flexível e facilmente desconectável contendo cabos e tubulação para transmissão de múltiplos serviços incluindo controle, energia, comunicação e injeção química.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An umbilical is an assembly that is a flexible and easily disconnectable bundle containing both cables and tubing for multi-service transmission including control, power, communication, and chemical injection.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b3317"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b3313"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b3314"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b3315"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b3316"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Umbilical(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃c,t,s,conn (CableBundle(c) ∧ TubingBundle(t) ∧ ProtectiveSheathing(s) ∧ ConnectorAssembly(conn) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,c) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,t) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,conn) ∧ hasQuality(x,Flexibility) ∧ hasQuality(x,EasyDisconnectability)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A device which is a flexible and easily disconnectable collection of cables and/or tubing for control, power, communication or chemical injection purposes.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;UMBILICAL&gt; is a &lt;DRILLING COMPONENT&gt; that is a flexible and easily disconnectable collection of cables and/or tubing for control, power, communication or chemical injection purposes.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A control line attached to a remove piece of equipment, usually a subsea wellhead, to provide hydraulic or electrical control, or inject small amounts of chemicals.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An assembly of hydraulic hoses which can also include electrical cables or optic fibres, used to control a sub sea structure or remote operated vehicle from a platform or a vessel.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">umbilical</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">umbilical</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive basis requires necessary conditions only. Under OWA, any assembly with cables, tubing, flexibility, and disconnectability could be forcibly classified as umbilical, including specialized multi-service bundles, complex wiring harnesses, or custom transmission assemblies that contain these elements but serve different industrial contexts and maintenance categories.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every umbilical is an assembly that has component parts including cable bundles and tubing bundles, and has the qualities of flexibility and easy disconnectability.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1122">
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1123"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1118"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/BraidedConductor">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">condutor de trançado</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">braided conductor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/VisualInspectionFunction">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000029"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2960"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2961"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">visual inspection function</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de inspeção visual</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in a VisualInspectionProcess and that consists in enabling direct optical observation of internal conditions, fluid properties, or process states within containers, vessels, or piping systems for operational monitoring, safety verification, or maintenance purposes.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000346">
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Shaft(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(PowerTransmissionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃k(ShaftKey(k) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,k)) ∧ ∃s(ShaftSeal(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)) ∧ ∃l(ShaftSleeve(l) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,l)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An Assembly that bears a PowerTransmissionFunction and that has component parts including shaft keys for torque transmission and shaft seals for leakage prevention, serving as the core rotating element in rotating machinery.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um Assembly que porta uma PowerTransmissionFunction e que possui partes componentes incluindo chavetas de eixo para transmissão de torque e vedações de eixo para prevenção de vazamento, servindo como o elemento rotativo central em máquinas rotativas.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2912"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2913"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2914"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2911"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">shaft</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">eixo</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every shaft is an assembly that transmits power through rotation and has shaft keys, shaft seals, and shaft sleeves as essential components.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification based on physical structure. Under OWA, sufficient conditions for shaft identity could lead to false positives - any assembly with a shaft key and rotational motion might be classified as a shaft rather than a more specific equipment type that contains a shaft. The structural differentia provides necessary conditions while allowing domain experts to validate sufficiency.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SHAFT&gt; is an &lt;ENGINE COMPONENT&gt; that is the core rotating element on which the rotating parts are mounted and through which energy is either transmitted from the prime mover or generated in case of a driver.</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2858">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/LiquidInlet"/>
