  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000363">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">TransmitterHousing ⊑ Assembly ⊓ ∃bearerOf.EnclosureFunction ⊓ ∃hasComponentPartAtAllTimes.TransmitterElectronicCircuit</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A transmitter housing is an Assembly that bears an EnclosureFunction and that has a transmitter electronic circuit as a component part at all times, designed to provide environmental protection and physical containment for transmitter components.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um invólucro de transmissor é uma Assembly que possui uma EnclosureFunction e que tem um circuito eletrônico de transmissor como parte componente em todos os momentos, projetado para fornecer proteção ambiental e contenção física para componentes do transmissor.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(TransmitterHousing(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(EnclosureFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃c(TransmitterElectronicCircuit(c) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,c)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">transmitter housing</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">invólucro de transmissor</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type based on physical structure as housing. Under OWA, sufficient conditions for transmitter housing would require specifying exact structural features (materials, dimensions, sealing mechanisms) that distinguish it from other instrument housings. The necessary conditions establish the core identity without risking false positives from other housing types that might share some structural features.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b3248"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;TRANSMITTER HOUSING&gt; is an &lt;INSTRUMENT HOUSING&gt; of a transmitter.</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b3212">
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b3208"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#nil"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2445">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FluidConductionFunction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000300">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] An artificial lift system that is powered by injected fluid (usually water), that powers a pump similar to the rotating pump used in electrical submersible pumps.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;HYDRAULIC PUMP&gt; is a &lt;POSITIVE DISPLACEMENT PUMP&gt; used in hydraulic drive systems and can be hydrostatic or hydrodynamic. It is a mechanical source of power that converts mechanical power into hydraulic energy (hydrostatic energy i.e. flow, pressure). It generates flow with enough power to overcome pressure induced by the load at the pump outlet. When a hydraulic pump operates, creates a vacuum at the pump inlet, which forces liquid from the reservoir into the inlet line to the pump and by mechanical action delivers this liquid to the pump outlet and forces it into the hydraulic system.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma bomba hidráulica é uma bomba de deslocamento positivo que converte energia mecânica em energia hidráulica para sistemas de acionamento hidráulico.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A hydraulic pump is a positive displacement pump that converts mechanical power into hydraulic energy for hydraulic drive systems.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every hydraulic pump is a positive displacement pump that bears a hydraulic pumping function and participates in hydraulic power transmission processes.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (HydraulicPump(x) ↔ PositiveDisplacementPump(x) ∧ ∃f(HydraulicPumpingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃p(HydraulicPowerTransmissionProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bomba hidráulica</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">hydraulic pump</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1917"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/LiquidOutlet">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">liquid outlet</rdfs:label>
