    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000286">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">turbina a gás</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gas turbine</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A turbine that compresses air which is then mixed with fuel for combustion and expansion through a turbine section to generate relatively high power output for either mechanical drive or power generation.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A turbine that compresses air which is then mixed with fuel for combustion and expansion through a turbine section to generate relatively high power output for either mechanical drive or power generation.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;GAS TURBINE&gt; is a &lt;TURBINE&gt; that compresses air which is then mixed with fuel for combustion and expansion through a turbine section to generate relatively high power output for either mechanical drive or power generation</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma turbina a gás é uma turbina que possui um compressor e câmara de combustão integrados, projetada para comprimir ar ambiente, misturá-lo com combustível para combustão, e expandir os gases quentes resultantes através de uma seção de turbina para gerar energia mecânica.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A gas turbine is a turbine that has an integrated compressor and combustion chamber, designed to compress ambient air, mix it with fuel for combustion, and expand the resulting hot gases through a turbine section to generate mechanical power.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every gas turbine is a turbine that has component parts compressor and combustion chamber at all times, and participates in air compression process and fuel combustion process.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1666"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(GasTurbine(x) ↔ Turbine(x) ∧ ∃c,h(Compressor(c) ∧ CombustionChamber(h) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,c) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,h)) ∧ ∃p1,p2(AirCompressionProcess(p1) ∧ FuelCombustionProcess(p2) ∧ participatesIn(x,p1) ∧ participatesIn(x,p2)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000251">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">elemento medidor de pressão diferencial</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">differential pressure measuring element</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b995"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A pressure element that bears a differential pressure measurement function and that consists in sensing the pressure difference between two fluid media or connection points to enable measurement of differential pressure through mechanical deflection proportional to the pressure difference.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um elemento de pressão que porta uma função de medição de pressão diferencial e que consiste em detectar a diferença de pressão entre duas mídias fluidas ou pontos de conexão para permitir a medição de pressão diferencial através de deflexão mecânica proporcional à diferença de pressão.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DIFFERENTIAL PRESSURE MEASURING ELEMENT&gt; is a &lt;PRESSURE MEASURING ELEMENT&gt; for the measurement of &lt;DIFFERENTIAL PRESSURE&gt;</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(DifferentialPressureMeasuringElement(x) ↔ (PressureElement(x) ∧ ∃f(DifferentialPressureMeasurementFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">DifferentialPressureMeasuringElement equivalentTo PressureElement and bearerOf some DifferentialPressureMeasurementFunction</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
