  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000310">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] The sensor component in a weight-indicator system that detects the tensional or compressional forces being imparted to the running string at surface.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;LOAD CELL&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;FORCE MEASURING ELEMENT&gt; and a &lt;TRANSDUCER&gt; that converts a force such as tension, compression, pressure, or torque into an electrical signal that can be measured</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A device based on strain gauge technology that helps measure the surface weight of coiled tubing.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A transducer which produces a signal with a defined relationship to the force applied to it.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma célula de carga é um instrumento que converte força mecânica (tração, compressão, pressão ou torque) em um sinal elétrico proporcional para fins de medição.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A load cell is an instrument that converts mechanical force (tension, compression, pressure, or torque) into a proportional electrical signal for measurement purposes.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">load cell</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">célula de carga</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every load cell is an instrument that bears a force-to-electrical transduction function and has a force-receiving element, transduction element, and electrical output.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (LoadCell(x) ↔ Instrument(x) ∧ ∃f(ForceToElectricalTransductionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b2180"/>
  </rdf:Description>
