  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000206">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;ACCUMULATOR&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that has a capability of &lt;ACCUMULATING&gt; matter and/or energy</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A functional object capable of storing energy, and which after discharge may be recharged.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object for storing energy, and which after discharge may be recharged.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] In context of a pressure control device, accumulators are canisters of hydraulic fluid, pressurized with a nitrogen gas cap of sufficient pressure and volume to operate all the rams on a BOP in case of power failure to the BOP.                  In context of a processing plant, an accumulator is a vessel that receives and temporarily stores a liquid used in the feed stock or the processing of a feed stream in a gas plant or other processing facility.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A device used in a hydraulic system to store energy or, in some applications, dampen pressure fluctuations.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um acumulador é um vaso que tem a função projetada de acumular (armazenar e liberar de forma controlada) energia ou matéria.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An accumulator is a vessel that has the designed function to accumulate (store and controllably release) energy or matter.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">acumulador</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">accumulator</rdfs:label>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000206"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every accumulator is a vessel that bears an accumulation function</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Accumulator(x) ↔ (Vessel(x) ∧ ∃f (AccumulationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b24"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/TemperatureSensorProtectionProcess">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a protective barrier shields a temperature sensing element from direct contact with the process medium while maintaining thermal conductivity to enable accurate temperature measurement.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de proteção de sensor de temperatura</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">temperature sensor protection process</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b3005">
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b3001"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b3006"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000217">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Boiler(x) ↔ Heater(x) ∧ ∃f(BoilingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;BOILER&gt; is a &lt;HEATER&gt; that brings a &lt;LIQUID&gt; to its boiling point</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[DEXPI] A that brings a liquid to its boiling point.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An indirect contact heat exchanger that is intended to heat a liquid.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">caldeira</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">boiler</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma caldeira é um aquecedor que leva um líquido ao seu ponto de ebulição através de troca de calor por contato indireto, produzindo vapor.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A boiler is a heater that brings a liquid to its boiling point through indirect contact heat exchange, producing steam or vapor.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b292"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every boiler is a heater that bears a BoilingFunction and has component parts including a steam drum and heat exchange surface.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/OutletConnection">
