  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000290">
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive differentia based on physical structure (toothed geometry). Under OWA, asserting equivalence could force classification of complex hybrid mechanisms or specialized toothed components that should not be categorized as standard gear wheels for maintenance purposes.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gear wheel</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">roda dentada</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um Assembly que porta uma PowerTransmissionFunction e que possui dentes circunferenciais para engajamento mecânico positivo com engrenagens ou cremalheiras correspondentes para transmitir movimento rotacional e potência.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An Assembly that bears a PowerTransmissionFunction and that has circumferential teeth for positive mechanical engagement with mating gears or racks to transmit rotational motion and power.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000121"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1737"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">GearWheel SubClassOf Assembly and (bearerOf some PowerTransmissionFunction) and (hasComponentPartAtAllTimes some Tooth) and (hasComponentPartAtAllTimes some WheelBody)</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(GearWheel(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(PowerTransmissionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃t(Tooth(t) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,t)) ∧ ∃w(WheelBody(w) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,w)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;GEAR WHEEL&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;TRANSMITTER(force)&gt; and that is a toothed wheel usend in conjunction with another, or with a rack, to transmit motion</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000282">
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b1612"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">fusível</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">fuse</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every fuse is an electrical equipment that bears a circuit protection function and has a fuse element that melts under overcurrent conditions.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A physical object that by the fusing of one or more of its specially designed and proportioned components, opens the circuit in which it is inserted by breaking the current when this exceeds a given value for a sufficient time.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that by the fusing of one or more of its specially designed and proportioned components, opens the circuit in which it is inserted by breaking the current when this exceeds a given value for a sufficient time.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FUSE&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;PROTECTOR&gt; and an &lt;ELECTRICAL ELEMENT&gt; that opens the circuit in which it is inserted by breaking the current when this exceeds a given value for a sufficient time</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Fuse(x) ↔ ElectricalEquipment(x) ∧ ∃f(CircuitProtectionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃e(FuseElement(e) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,e)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um fusível é um equipamento elétrico que protege circuitos interrompendo o fluxo de corrente através do derretimento intencional de um elemento fusível quando a corrente excede valores especificados por uma duração suficiente.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A fuse is an electrical equipment that protects circuits by interrupting current flow through the intentional melting of a fusible element when current exceeds specified values for a sufficient duration.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="n297d145abb684750972df9e3ef9e1556b3462">
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/WellSurfaceControlProcess"/>
